<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.1//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml11/DTD/xhtml11.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
 <head>
  <title>CSS Test: margin-box - bottom-right/left width</title>
  <link rel="author" title="Tom Clancy" href="mailto:tclancy@revenution.com"/>
  <link rel="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/css3-page/#margin-boxes"/>
  <meta name="flags" content="paged" />
  <meta name="assert" content="If the bottom-center box is not empty or its computed width is not 'auto' then the outer widths of the bottom-left and bottom-right boxes are equal"/>
  <style type="text/css"><![CDATA[
   @page {
   		@bottom-center { 
			content: "x";
			border: 1pt solid black; 
			margin: 16pt;
			margin-bottom: 0.25in;
		}
		@bottom-left { 
			content: "";
			border: 1pt solid black; 
			width: 2in;
			margin-bottom: 0.25in;
		}
		@bottom-right { 
			content: "";
			border: 1pt solid black; 
			width: 3in;
			margin-bottom: 0.25in;
		}
   }
  ]]></style>
 </head>
 <body>
  <p>There should be three boxes at the bottom of this page. The one in the middle contains an 'x' which must be centered with respect to the page width.</p>
 </body>
</html>